<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-17T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="265" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">138 Spain/932: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-17T19:00:00-04:00">May 17, 1938—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>442. Consulate’s 16th re passports. You are authorized in your discretion
                            take up matter with Ministry of State and to take any other action which
                            might result in recovery of any of passports.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>